Package com.CZ2002.entities

Class Reservation

java.lang.Object
com.CZ2002.entities.RestaurantEntity
com.CZ2002.entities.Reservation
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Reservation extends RestaurantEntity
The Reservation class represents a booking made at the restaurant. A reservation must be specified by a name, contact number, pax, table number and reservation period and can be identified by using these attributes.

The Reservation class is designed to only hold all data related to a reservation and should not implement any logic in relation to reservations.

    • Reservation

      public Reservation(GregorianCalendar reservationPeriod, int pax, String name, String contactNumber, int tableNo)
      Constructs a new reservation that represents the booking made for a particular time.

      This constructor initialises the expiry of the reservation to null.

      Parameters:
      reservationPeriod - the GregorianCalendar start time of this reservation
      pax - the number of guests
      name - the String to address the contact person
      contactNumber - the String representing the phone number to contact the guest at
      tableNo - the table number reserved

    • getExpiry

      public ScheduledFuture<Void> getExpiry()
      Gets the ScheduledFuture that triggers this reservation's expiry. The expiry should be cancelled by calling Future.cancel(boolean) on the ScheduledFuture returned by this method if this reservation is cancelled or its reservation period has been changed.
      Returns:
      the ScheduledFuture representing the pending expiry of a reservation
